<doc>
  <member name="D3D12_BOX">
    <summary>
      <para>Describes a 3D box.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>This structure is used by the methods <see cref="WriteToSubresource" />, <see cref="ReadFromSubresource" /> and <see cref="CopyTextureRegion" />.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d12/cd3dx12-box">CD3DX12_BOX</seealso>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d12/direct3d-12-structures">Core Structures</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_BOX.left">
    <summary>
      <para>The x position of the left hand side of the box.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_BOX.top">
    <summary>
      <para>The y position of the top of the box.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_BOX.front">
    <summary>
      <para>The z position of the front of the box.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_BOX.right">
    <summary>
      <para>The x position of the right hand side of the box, plus 1. This means that <code>right - left</code> equals the width of the box.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_BOX.bottom">
    <summary>
      <para>The y position of the bottom of the box, plus 1. This means that <code>bottom - top</code> equals the height of the box.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_BOX.back">
    <summary>
      <para>The z position of the back of the box, plus 1. This means that <code>back - front</code> equals the depth of the box.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>